Theory:
Conditional Statements:
-- To make the set of instructions execute only when the given
   condition is true
-- they are used to decide whether the code has to be executed or 
   Skip based on the given condition.
-- line by line sequence of execution.

Block of code:set of instructions:
--it will execute only when that specific Conditon is true.

Conditon:An expression that evalautes an result(True or false)
Ex:console.log(5>6)

--Methods:
if
if -else
else if
switch
ternary operator 

if: only one possible Condition:
